The paper also involves algorithmic results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper cites several results on graph theory and combinatorics, which could make cs.GT (Graph Theory) a likely sub-category as well.
